## Issue 6: Excess Chrome launches

**Root cause**: `SessionManager::create()` in session.rs:54-83 unconditionally calls `CdpBackend::launch()` on every invocation. Each `AgentLoop.run()` (loop.py:143-148) creates a new session per goal. There is no session pooling or reuse anywhere — N goals = N Chromium instances. Chrome launch takes ~1-2 seconds and consumes ~100-300 MB RAM per instance.

**Fix -- crates/ans-ipc/src/session.rs, lines 52-84** (`SessionManager::create`):

Add idle-session reuse by checking for an existing idle session with the same goal_id:

```rust
/// Create a new session or reuse an existing idle one.
/// Reuses: navigates the existing session to `start_url` if provided.
/// Creates: launches a fresh Chromium instance.
pub async fn create(
    &self,
    goal_id: Uuid,
    start_url: Option<String>,
) -> Result<Uuid, BrowserError> {
    // Reuse: check for existing idle session for this goal
    {
        let sessions = self.sessions.read().await;
        for handle in sessions.values() {
            if handle.goal_id == goal_id
                && handle.status == SessionStatus::Idle
            {
                let session_id = handle.session_id;
                tracing::info!(%session_id, "Reusing existing idle session for goal");
                // Navigate to new start URL if needed
                if let Some(ref url) = start_url {
                    if handle.current_url != *url {
                        drop(sessions); // release read lock before navigate
                        let _ = self.navigate(session_id, url).await;
                    }
                }
                return Ok(session_id);
            }
        }
    }

    // Create: no reusable session found
    let session_id = Uuid::new_v4();
    tracing::info!(%session_id, %goal_id, "Creating new session");

    let backend = CdpBackend::launch(Some(StealthConfig::standard())).await?;

    if let Some(url) = &start_url {
        let _ = backend
            .navigate(url, Duration::from_secs(10))
            .await
            .map(|state| {
                tracing::info!(url = %state.url, "Session started at URL");
            });
    }

    let handle = SessionHandle {
        session_id,
        goal_id,
        backend,
        current_url: start_url.unwrap_or_else(|| "about:blank".into()),
        status: SessionStatus::Idle,
    };

    self.sessions.write().await.insert(session_id, handle);

    Ok(session_id)
}
```

**Also fix -- loop.py, lines 143-148**: When `daemon_goal_id` is provided (daemon-spawned mode), try to reuse the existing session for that goal instead of always creating new:

```python
# 0. Create or reuse browser session
session = await self._grpc.create_session(
    goal_id=effective_goal_id,
)
```

This works because `create_session` in the Rust layer now reuses idle sessions with the same `goal_id`. The Python side needs no changes — the reuse is transparent at the gRPC level.

